    <stitle>EC-30 ABS / ATC CONTROLLER - MOUNTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MOUNTING</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>ECU Only</title>
            <para>The EC-30 can be bracket mounted to the vehicle cab or chassis as a stand alone ECU. See
                <hotlnk document="s04043_1.xml" xrefid="f0404301">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Valve Mounted EC-30</title>
            <para>The EC-30 can be assembled on one of four different valve models. The controller valve assembly is
                then mounted in place of the standard service brake relay valve on the vehicle. An assembly model
                designation is assigned when the EC-30 is mounted on an AR (antilock relay) valve or an ATR
                (antilock/traction relay) valve. See
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404302">Figure 2</hotlnk>. Some models include bobtail proportioning and/or ATC
                functions. See
                <hotlnk xrefid="t0404302">Table 2</hotlnk>.
            </para>
